From: Ian Campbell <ian.campbell@citrix.com>
Subject: xen/netback: Allow setting of large MTU before rings have connected
Patch-mainline: n/a

This allows large MTU to be configured by the VIF hotplug script.
Previously this would fail because at the point the hotplug script
runs the VIF features have most likely not been negotiated with the
frontend and so SG has not yet been enabled. Invert this behaviour
so that SG is assumed present until negotiations prove otherwise and
reduce MTU at that point.

Signed-off-by: Ian Campbell <ian.campbell@citrix.com>
Acked-by: jbeulich@novell.com

